Police Minister Bheki Cele has described the killing of 28-year-old Hilary Gardee as a brutal murder. She was abducted with her 3-year-old child on Friday. The child was later left roaming around in Kamagugu, Nelspruit. eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones has more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The EFF is warning if they find the killers of Hillary Gardee before the police do, there are no guarantees of what will happen to them. The party says the death of the daughter of its former Secretary-General Goodrich Gardee has caused the family grief. The 28-year-old's body was found on Tuesday. READ: Hillary Gardee shot execution-style, says family spokesperson She had been missing since last Friday. Meanwhile, the cops are working against the clock to make an arrest before the 72-hour activation deadline set for Tuesday. * eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones reports.